The Chairman of Mbong Emmanuel Essien Foundation, Mr. Mbong Emmanuel Essien has described the Victory of Governor Udom Emmanuel of Akwa Ibom State at the governorship election petition tribunal sitting in Uyo as a victory for all Akwa Ibomite. In a chat with our correspondent, Mr. Essien noted that the People of Akwa Ibom state unanimously voted for the Peopleâ€™s Democratic Party during the March 23 general election. He urged Obong Nsima Ekere and the All Progressive Congress (APC) to accept the tribunal rulling in good faith and join Governor Emmanuel in the development of Akwa Ibom State. According to him, with the pronouncement of the judiciary all the potential distractions over the election should be put to rest. Mr. Essien urged Governor Emmanuel to extends a hand of fellowship to those who felt aggrieved at the outcome of the election, and commended the judiciary for giving the verdict without any fear nor favor. Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook 